title: SFH on avian influenza A(H7N9) (with photos)
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after meeting the representatives of local live 
	poultry trade this afternoon (January 28): Reporter: (on the suggestions raised by live poultry trade at the meeting) Secretary for Food and Health: The industry proposed that the Government 
	should consider establishing another poultry wholesale market, so that 
	imported poultry population can be separated from local poultry population. 
	The Government has reservation in establishing another wholesale market. We

The Government has reservation in establishing another wholesale market. We 
	pointed out to the industry that barring other policy considerations, there 
	are genuine technical difficulties in identifying a suitable place for such 
	a purpose. On top of that, even if we come up with a possible site for such 
	a purpose, we anticipate resistance or objection from various districts with 
	reasonable grounds. Therefore, it will not be easy. However, we do reckon 
	that if possible, we should explore a mechanism so that when the imported

that if possible, we should explore a mechanism so that when the imported 
	poultry is awaiting the test results, they do not have to be placed at the 
	same site with local poultry. Regarding the long term policy as to whether Hong Kong would still like to 
	have live chicken supply, I think it is time for the whole community to 
	rethink in the light of the recent incident. (Please also refer to the
	<a href="../../../../cn/press_and_publications/press/2014/press140128.htm">

Chinese portion of the transcript.) Ends/Tuesday, January 28, 2014
Issued at HKT 22:14
